maps3end

This Python package provides some basic scripts to analyze data from MAPS, a method in the family of 3'-end RNA-seq developed in Fu Lab at UCSD.

Quick start
1. Install two dependent Python packages below (by pip, for example): 
  pysam: https://code.google.com/p/pysam/
  HTSeq: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/HTSeq
2. Add path/to/maps3end to your PYTHONPATH
3. Try scripts under maps3end/scripts/

It has been run on Python 2.6.5 and 2.7.2.

Please send an email to Yu Zhou (y6zhou@ucsd.edu) if you find any problem or have any suggestion. 


Kent source packages can be downloaded from here.
http://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/jksrc.zip


